metadata.name: Motion to Emotion
metadata.description:
Mental affects one's ability to manage feelings and deal with everyday difficulties.

When you move, your body releases endorphins that help relieve stress and improve your mood before and after exercise. That's why exercise is a powerful antidote to stress, anxiety, and depression.

A few small rhythms filled with repetitive movements in the hope of giving new positive emotions in the soul, are a few small examples of the many seeds that we can cultivate in an Emotional state on mental health.
